---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const sections = [
  { label: 'How It Works', id: 'overview' },
  { label: 'Billing', id: 'billing' },
  { label: 'Medication & Pricing', id: 'pricing' },
  { label: 'Refill Cycle', id: 'refill' },
  { label: 'Fulfillment', id: 'fulfillment' },
  { label: 'Plan Changes', id: 'plan-changes' },
  { label: 'Cancellation', id: 'cancellation' },
  { label: 'Edge Cases', id: 'edge-cases' },
];

const monthly = 'inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-teal/10 text-teal text-xs font-semibold';
const commitment = 'inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-terracotta/10 text-terracotta text-xs font-semibold';
const allPlans = 'inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-dark/8 text-dark/60 text-xs font-semibold';
const decided = 'inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-teal/10 text-teal text-xs font-medium gap-1';
const pending = 'inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-xs font-medium gap-1';
---

<Layout title="Billing, Refill & Fulfillment" active="fulfillment" sections={sections}>
  <div class="max-w-[860px] mx-auto px-10 py-16">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-14">
      <p class="font-inter text-teal text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">WeightWise</p>
      <h1 class="font-fraunces text-4xl font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-4">Billing, Refill & Fulfillment</h1>
      <p class="font-inter text-dark/50 text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-[580px]">
        How the money moves, how medication ships, and how the refill cycle works — distilled for quick reference.
      </p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mt-6">
        <span class={monthly}>Monthly</span>
        <span class={commitment}>3 / 6-month</span>
        <span class={allPlans}>All plans</span>
        <span class="font-inter text-dark/30 text-xs">— plan type indicators used throughout</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ─── HOW IT WORKS (overview) ─── -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-6">How It Works at a Glance</h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div class="bg-teal/8 border border-teal/15 rounded-2xl p-5">
          <p class={`${monthly} mb-3`}>Monthly</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Pay as you engage</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/60 text-sm leading-relaxed">Card held on file at signup — <strong>no charge until your provider writes a prescription</strong>. Every 28 days, complete a check-in → provider reviews → prescription issued → <em>then</em> you're charged.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-terracotta/8 border border-terracotta/15 rounded-2xl p-5">
          <p class={`${commitment} mb-3`}>3 / 6-Month</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Pay upfront in full</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/60 text-sm leading-relaxed">Full 3 or 6-month cost charged immediately at signup. Monthly check-ins still required to release each shipment. <strong>Klarna/Afterpay</strong> integration planned to make this digestible at checkout.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Quick facts -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-3">
        {[
          { label: 'Medication cycle', value: '28 days', sub: '1 shot/week' },
          { label: 'Monthly inactivity cutoff', value: 'Day 44', sub: '5:00 PM CT' },
          { label: 'Commitment inactivity', value: 'End of\nbilling period', sub: '11:59 PM CT' },
          { label: '3/6-mo intake deadline', value: '7 days', sub: 'then auto-refund' },
        ].map(f => (
          <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-4 text-center">
            <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-xs mb-1">{f.label}</p>
            <p class="font-fraunces text-xl font-semibold text-dark whitespace-pre-line leading-tight">{f.value}</p>
            <p class="font-inter text-dark/30 text-xs mt-1">{f.sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── BILLING ─── -->
    <section id="billing" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-6">Billing Rules</h2>

      <div class="space-y-3">

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class={monthly}>Monthly</span>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">First charge = when provider approves prescription</p>
              </div>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Card authorized at signup. Charge captured only when the provider creates a recommendation after the initial intake encounter. If auth window expires before the encounter finishes, the system re-authorizes silently. If the card is declined at charge time → enter payment failure flow (subscription valid 30 days).</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class={commitment}>3 / 6-Month</span>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">First charge = at signup, immediately</p>
              </div>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Full upfront payment at subscription purchase. If provider determines patient is not suitable after first payment → automatic full refund, Nimbus absorbs the encounter cost. If intake never completed → auto-refund after 7 days. No prescription released until payment is confirmed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class={monthly}>Monthly</span>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">Recurring billing = 28-day cycle, charge at prescription</p>
              </div>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Billed every 28 days — aligned to 1 shot/week schedule. Next cycle starts from the date of payment, not original signup date. Early check-in shifts the next cycle. No prescription issued if intake is not completed — this is a regulatory requirement, not just policy.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class={commitment}>3 / 6-Month</span>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">Recurring billing = not applicable — already paid in full</p>
              </div>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Commitment users paid upfront. Monthly check-ins still required to release each shipment — but no new charges occur during the term. Commitment clock starts at payment. If check-in missed, shipment for that month is forfeited — they bought 3/6 months of care, not a guaranteed number of vials.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class={allPlans}>All plans</span>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">Payment failure → Stripe Smart Retries + dunning sequence</p>
              </div>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Monthly: if first payment fails at signup, patient is blocked and asked for a new payment method — no grace period at signup. For recurring failures: Stripe Smart Retries → Day +7 email → Day +14 email → Inactive at end of billing period. There is no manual 7-day grace period; the retry cadence is automated via Stripe webhooks.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-500 text-base mt-0.5">⚡</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-inter text-amber-900 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Coming soon: Klarna + Afterpay + HSA messaging</p>
              <p class="font-inter text-amber-800/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">These integrations are required before pushing for higher 3/6-month adoption. Afterpay/Klarna should be integrated as soon as possible to make upfront costs digestible. HSA eligibility messaging needs to appear on the pricing page.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── PRICING ─── -->
    <section id="pricing" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Medication & Pricing</h2>
      <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-sm mb-6">Two medications, both compound GLP-1 — different active ingredients and price points.</p>

      <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden mb-4">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-4 bg-warm-gray/50 border-b border-dark/8 px-5 py-3">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/50 text-xs font-semibold col-span-2">Medication</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-teal text-xs font-semibold text-center">Monthly</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/50 text-xs font-semibold text-center">3-mo / 6-mo</p>
        </div>
        {[
          { name: 'CarniSema®', sub: 'Semaglutide', monthly: '$179/mo', commit: '$149 / $129' },
          { name: 'CarniTide®', sub: 'Tirzepatide', monthly: '$299/mo', commit: '$249 / $219' },
        ].map(med => (
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 px-5 py-4 border-b border-dark/5 last:border-0">
            <div class="col-span-2">
              <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">{med.name}</p>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-xs">{med.sub}</p>
            </div>
            <p class="font-inter text-dark/70 text-sm text-center self-center">{med.monthly}</p>
            <p class="font-inter text-dark/50 text-sm text-center self-center">{med.commit} /mo</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Switching medications</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-xs leading-relaxed">Preference-only switch → takes effect next cycle at new drug's rate. Clinical necessity switch (severe adverse effects) → immediate, charge the price difference this month only, new rate from following month onward.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Price acknowledgment required</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-xs leading-relaxed">Any medication switch that changes the cost requires a <strong>mandatory price acknowledgment screen</strong> before the switch is confirmed. This is a hard gate — FTC compliance and chargeback protection. No exceptions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── REFILL CYCLE ─── -->
    <section id="refill" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Refill Cycle</h2>
      <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-sm mb-6">28-day cycle, driven by intake completion — not calendar dates.</p>

      <!-- Timeline -->
      <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-4">
        <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-5">Monthly refill timeline</p>
        <div class="relative">
          <!-- line -->
          <div class="absolute top-3.5 left-0 right-0 h-px bg-dark/10"></div>
          <div class="relative grid grid-cols-6 gap-1">
            {[
              { day: 'Day 0', label: 'Last shipment', color: 'bg-teal' },
              { day: 'Day 18', label: 'Refill window opens', color: 'bg-dark/20' },
              { day: 'Day 20', label: 'Reminder #1', color: 'bg-amber-300' },
              { day: 'Day 28', label: 'Reminder #2\n"Do it today"', color: 'bg-amber-400' },
              { day: 'Day 33', label: 'Final warning', color: 'bg-red-300' },
              { day: 'Day 44', label: 'Inactive\n5:00 PM CT', color: 'bg-red-500' },
            ].map(t => (
              <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2 relative">
                <div class={`w-3 h-3 rounded-full ${t.color} flex-shrink-0 z-10`}></div>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-xs text-center">{t.day}</p>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-xs text-center whitespace-pre-line leading-snug">{t.label}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="font-inter text-dark/30 text-xs mt-5 border-t border-dark/6 pt-4">The Day 20 nudge gives patients <strong class="text-dark/50">24 days of runway</strong> before the Day 44 deadline. By Day 44, the system has already given clinical review + fulfillment (5 business days) enough time to complete.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-3">

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Monthly: missed check-in → automatic resume when completed</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Late check-in (Day +1 to +43) triggers an automatic resume — no CS intervention needed. Provider reviews, charges, and ships as normal. The <strong>next cycle starts from the date of payment</strong>, not the original schedule. No gap compensation or credits.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
            <span class={commitment}>3 / 6-Month</span>
            <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">Missed check-in = missed shipment, no refund</p>
          </div>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Commitment users bought 3/6 months of <em>care</em>, not a guaranteed number of vials. Monthly check-in is required to release each shipment. If missed, that month's shipment is forfeited. No credit, no compensation. This will be messaged clearly at signup: <em>"Regardless if you have meds leftover, do your refill today — per USP, every vial should be discarded after 28 days of first puncture."</em></p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Inactivity deadlines by plan</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-2">
            <div class="bg-teal/5 rounded-lg p-3">
              <p class={`${monthly} mb-2`}>Monthly</p>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">Day 44 at 5:00 PM CT</p>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/50 text-xs mt-1">Triggered if intake not completed. Clock starts at last shipment date. Nudge sequence starts Day 20.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-terracotta/5 rounded-lg p-3">
              <p class={`${commitment} mb-2`}>3 / 6-Month</p>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">End of billing period at 11:59 PM CT</p>
              <p class="font-inter text-dark/50 text-xs mt-1">Payment-driven via Stripe webhooks. If payment unresolved after Smart Retry dunning sequence.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── FULFILLMENT ─── -->
    <section id="fulfillment" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Fulfillment</h2>
      <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-sm mb-6">From provider approval to medication at the door.</p>

      <div class="space-y-3">

        <div class="bg-dark/4 border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔒 No intake = no prescription. Full stop.</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">This is a regulatory requirement — not discretionary policy. Providers cannot write a prescription without a completed intake. Engineering must enforce this as a hard gate; it cannot be bypassed by any plan type or billing state.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-3">What happens after provider review</p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            {[
              { outcome: 'Approves — same dose', action: 'Order placed automatically. MDI sends prescription approval notification to patient.' },
              { outcome: 'Adjusts dose', action: 'Provider decides, patient is informed after. No consent needed (price doesn\'t change by dose).' },
              { outcome: 'Recommends stopping treatment', action: 'Provider documents reason. If it meets refund criteria, subscription cancelled + refund issued.' },
              { outcome: 'Recommends medication switch', action: 'Patient must see mandatory price acknowledgment screen and confirm before switch is logged.' },
            ].map(r => (
              <div class="flex gap-3 py-2 border-b border-dark/5 last:border-0">
                <div class="w-[160px] flex-shrink-0">
                  <p class="font-inter text-dark/60 text-xs font-semibold">{r.outcome}</p>
                </div>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-xs leading-relaxed">{r.action}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Internal pharmacy states are not patient-facing</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">ORD_01 (Sent to Pharmacy), ORD_02 (Acknowledged), ORD_03 (Being Filled) — no notifications sent for these. They surface as a visual progress tracker in the patient portal only. First patient-facing notification is when the order <strong>ships</strong>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Split shipments (BUD — medication freshness)</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Large orders may be split into multiple shipments to ensure medication potency (Beyond-Use Date requirements). When this happens, the patient receives an explanation email so they don't open a support ticket. Shipment 2+ is timed to arrive before the first supply runs out.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Minimum viable turnaround assumption: 5 business days</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">The nudge sequence assumes: Day 2 provider approval → Day 7 delivery. As long as this holds, the Day 20 first nudge provides sufficient lead time. If fulfillment ever runs longer than 5 business days, the notification timing must be revisited.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── PLAN CHANGES ─── -->
    <section id="plan-changes" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Plan Changes & Commitment Rules</h2>
      <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-sm mb-6">The guiding principle: no mid-cycle changes, no exceptions.</p>

      <div class="space-y-3">

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-warm-gray/40 px-5 py-3 border-b border-dark/8">
            <p class="font-inter text-dark/60 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest">Subscription length changes</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5 space-y-3">
            {[
              { rule: 'Monthly → 3/6-month upgrade', decision: 'No mid-plan changes. Patient can upgrade at renewal. A $100 offer is available to incentivize upgrade at that time.' },
              { rule: '3-month → 6-month', decision: 'Not permitted mid-term. Must wait for current term to end.' },
              { rule: '3/6-month → monthly downgrade', decision: 'Only allowed if patient meets strict criteria per the Refund Policy. Engineering should gate the cancel/downgrade option behind an eligibility check.' },
            ].map(r => (
              <div class="flex gap-4 py-2 border-b border-dark/5 last:border-0">
                <div class="w-[220px] flex-shrink-0">
                  <p class="font-inter text-dark/70 text-xs font-semibold">{r.rule}</p>
                </div>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-xs leading-relaxed">{r.decision}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-warm-gray/40 px-5 py-3 border-b border-dark/8">
            <p class="font-inter text-dark/60 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest">Drug / medication changes</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5 space-y-3">
            {[
              { rule: 'Preference switch (any plan)', decision: 'Takes effect at next cycle. New rate applies from next cycle at that drug\'s commitment price. No proration. No mid-cycle changes once intake received and shipment sent to pharmacy.' },
              { rule: 'Clinical necessity switch', decision: 'Immediate — sends new vial, charges the price difference for current month only. Following months reflect the new drug\'s full rate.' },
              { rule: 'Commitment rate during switch', decision: 'Term clock continues — only the price changes. Patient does not start a new commitment.' },
            ].map(r => (
              <div class="flex gap-4 py-2 border-b border-dark/5 last:border-0">
                <div class="w-[220px] flex-shrink-0">
                  <p class="font-inter text-dark/70 text-xs font-semibold">{r.rule}</p>
                </div>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-xs leading-relaxed">{r.decision}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Commitment auto-renewal</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">3/6-month plans auto-renew into the same term at the same rate. Patient is notified 7 days before renewal. If they do nothing → auto-renews. If they cancel or change before the renewal date → their decision applies from next term. No billing surprises.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── CANCELLATION ─── -->
    <section id="cancellation" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Cancellation</h2>
      <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-sm mb-6">Making cancellation easy builds trust. No guilt, no hidden fees, no blocked flows.</p>

      <div class="space-y-3">

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
            <span class={monthly}>Monthly</span>
            <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">Can cancel anytime — simple, clean</p>
          </div>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Subscription stays active until end of current billing cycle. No further charges after. Two edge cases: if they cancel <em>after</em> completing a check-in but before provider reviews → complete the encounter, charge this final cycle, then cancel. If they cancel after charge but before shipment → medication still ships, then subscription ends.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
            <span class={commitment}>3 / 6-Month</span>
            <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">Cancellation only via Refund Policy criteria</p>
          </div>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Commitment is a commitment. Standard cancellations are not offered in the portal UI for 3/6-month subscribers. Engineering should gate the cancellation option behind a refund policy eligibility check — if criteria aren't met, the option is not available. CS handles exceptions per the Refund Policy doc.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Restart after cancellation or inactivity</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed"><strong>No full re-enrollment required.</strong> Inactive state has a direct resume path: payment + questionnaire → Active–Pending Fulfillment. Existing patient record and medical history retained. The portal should show the restart CTA prominently without requiring a new intake from scratch.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── EDGE CASES ─── -->
    <section id="edge-cases" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-8">
      <h2 class="font-fraunces text-2xl font-semibold text-dark mb-6">Edge Cases & Decisions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-3">

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Provider declines patient as clinically unsuitable</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Applies to both monthly (pre-charge) and 3/6-month (already paid). CS manually refunds. Nimbus absorbs the provider visit cost. This is an established process — no open questions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">3/6-month: commitment clock start date</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Clock starts <strong>at payment</strong> — not at first shipment or intake completion. If intake takes 5 days, those 5 days count against the commitment term.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Migration: existing users moving to new billing model</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Legacy billing continues through the current subscription cycle — no pause, no mid-cycle adjustment. At next renewal, patient is notified of new flat-rate pricing. No retroactive credits. ~83% of current subscribers (1,001 monthly users) are expected to convert within a month of launch. The remaining 17% are on 2/3/6-month terms that will naturally expire.</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-2 mt-3">
            {[
              { label: 'Monthly (83%)', val: '1,001 subs', rev: '$231K/mo' },
              { label: '3-month (9%)', val: '114 subs', rev: '$12K/mo' },
              { label: '6-month (6%)', val: '66 subs', rev: '$8K/mo' },
              { label: '2-month (2%)', val: '24 subs', rev: '$1K/mo' },
            ].map(s => (
              <div class="bg-warm-gray/50 rounded-lg p-3 text-center">
                <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-xs mb-1">{s.label}</p>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm">{s.val}</p>
                <p class="font-inter text-dark/40 text-xs">{s.rev}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Plan changes during migration (active orders)</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">If a patient has an active order or open encounter during migration → that cycle completes under old billing rules. New plan takes effect next cycle. A migration event does not override mid-cycle rules.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-dark/8 rounded-xl p-5">
          <p class="font-inter text-dark font-semibold text-sm mb-2">28-day vs 30-day billing gap</p>
          <p class="font-inter text-dark/55 text-sm leading-relaxed">Medication supply = 28 days (1 shot/week). Monthly billing = 28-day cycles (not calendar month). This eliminates the supply-vs-billing gap entirely. Key messaging: <em>"Regardless of whether you have medication left over, discard and reorder after 28 days of first puncture"</em> — per USP guidelines.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
